Class TreeEvalVisitor

  • java.lang.Object
    • TreeEvalVisitor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Visitor

    public class TreeEvalVisitor
extends java.lang.Object
implements Visitor
    Class TreeEvalVisitor is an implementation of the Visitor interface. It defines the visit method for all node types, using the rootVal member to keep track of the result of the subtree which is currently being visited.
    Author:
    Diana
